Rather than caste, en=
vironment in which one grows up does have a role (and caste does sometimes =
influence the family environment in India). One born in a family (brahmana =
or otherwise) that worships god everyday is exposed to that notion. One bro=
ught up in a family that cares a little about god or morality and pursues m=
oney or power or comforts ruthlessly is exposed that notion. So the religio=
us/spiritual aspects of the environment in which one grows up do play a rol=
e. However, if one has strong vasanas, they will eventually take hold. One =
will meet people who make those vasanas flourish and those vasanas take con=
trol.

